In [12]:
#compare CodedMonth and month_year
print('the number of rows that codedmonth and month_year are different :', df[(df['CodedMonth']!=df['month_year'])].shape[0])
print('the number of rows that codedmonth bigger than month_year and month_tear < 2018-01 :',df[(df['CodedMonth']>df['month_year']) & (df['month_year']<'2018-01')].shape[0])
print('the number of rows that codedmonth bigger than month_year and month_tear >= 2018-01 :',df[(df['CodedMonth']>df['month_year']) & (df['month_year']>='2018-01')].shape[0])

the number of rows that codedmonth and month_year are different : 4402
the number of rows that codedmonth bigger than month_year and month_tear < 2018-01 : 947
the number of rows that codedmonth bigger than month_year and month_tear >= 2018-01 : 3455

From above analysis, we can find CodedMonth and DataOccur are different, there are 4402 CodedMonth > DataOccur. But the record data are all from CodedMonth. So I would keep the rows which DateOccur >=2018-01. Because there are 947 rows that the actual crime happens before 2017. Which would be useless in the analysis. Also, the time for the future analysis will use the column 'month_year'¶

In [31]:
for i in range(10):
    lat = map_data['Raw_String'].iloc[i][0]
    long = map_data['Raw_String'].iloc[i][1]
    location=map_data['address'].iloc[i]
    if map_data['ValueCount'].iloc[i] > 150:
        color = 'red'
    elif map_data['ValueCount'].iloc[i] >= 100:
        color = 'orange'
    elif map_data['ValueCount'].iloc[i] < 100:
        color = 'blue'
    
    popup_text = """
                Location: {}<br>
                Peace Disruptions : {}<br>"""
    popup_text = popup_text.format(
                               location, 
                               map_data['ValueCount'].iloc[i]
                               )
    folium.Marker(location = [lat, long], popup= popup_text,icon=folium.Icon(color= color)).add_to(stl_crime_street)

plt.tick_params(labelsize=16);

Here, the noticable trend is a rise in curve at the start of the year and achieveing the peak at the mid point. somehwhere at August . After that it has an equally sharp drop to the initial number of crimes as the year started.¶

stl_crime_map=folium.Map(location=[38.64, -90.2],
                        zoom_start=10.5)
for i in range(500):
    lat = map_data['Raw_String'].iloc[i][0]
    long = map_data['Raw_String'].iloc[i][1]
    location=map_data['address'].iloc[i]
    radius = map_data['ValueCount'].iloc[i] /5
    
    if map_data['ValueCount'].iloc[i] > 20:
        color = "#FF4500"
    else:
        color = "#008080"
    
    popup_text = """Latitude : {}<br>
                Longitude : {}<br>
                Location: {}<br>
                Peace Disruptions : {}<br>"""
    popup_text = popup_text.format(lat,
                               long,
                               location, 
                               map_data['ValueCount'].iloc[i]
                               )
    folium.CircleMarker(location = [lat, long], popup= popup_text,radius = radius, color = color, fill = True).add_to(stl_crime_map)
